{"id": "ChIJ5WOlQwClwoARJ-E8naRZCbU", "rating": 4.7, "userRatingCount": 342, "displayName": {"text": "Petitgrain Boulangerie", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJ5WOlQwClwoARJ-E8naRZCbU/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWT1ptTm9YMkpUTlhKRE9FUkJhWE5hUm1aSVpGRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Petitgrain Boulangerie was named one of “the best bakeries in the country right now” by The Infatuation — and honestly? It didn’t just live up to the hype, it baked it into a perfect croissant and served it warm. Yes, there’s usually a line, but it’s never more than 20–25 minutes, aka, less time than I’ve waited for worse things. Metered parking out front or nearby street spots make it easy.\n\nEverything I’ve tried is a 5/5. The cinnamon roll, pain aux raisin (raisin bread), lemon pistachio croissant, pain aux chocolate (chocolate bread), quiche, and jambon gruyere (ham and Gruyère cheese). Even the “worst” thing here (looking at you, blueberry scone) would be the best item at another fancy bakery. Items rotate, so bring a backup craving — they will sell out.  Also, I love that they buy their organic flours and local produce from Santa Monica Farmers Market.\n\nI wouldn't wake up at 6 AM if it were my wedding day, but I'd gladly do so for a heavenly bite of one of Petitgrain's pastries.  Eating their baked goods is like a religious experience for me, albeit, I'm not religious - pastries so divine they could convert me. Four visits in eight weeks... and counting.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Petitgrain Boulangerie was named one of “the best bakeries in the country right now” by The Infatuation — and honestly? It didn’t just live up to the hype, it baked it into a perfect croissant and served it warm. Yes, there’s usually a line, but it’s never more than 20–25 minutes, aka, less time than I’ve waited for worse things. Metered parking out front or nearby street spots make it easy.\n\nEverything I’ve tried is a 5/5. The cinnamon roll, pain aux raisin (raisin bread), lemon pistachio croissant, pain aux chocolate (chocolate bread), quiche, and jambon gruyere (ham and Gruyère cheese). Even the “worst” thing here (looking at you, blueberry scone) would be the best item at another fancy bakery. Items rotate, so bring a backup craving — they will sell out.  Also, I love that they buy their organic flours and local produce from Santa Monica Farmers Market.\n\nI wouldn't wake up at 6 AM if it were my wedding day, but I'd gladly do so for a heavenly bite of one of Petitgrain's pastries.  Eating their baked goods is like a religious experience for me, albeit, I'm not religious - pastries so divine they could convert me. Four visits in eight weeks... and counting.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Mike P", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114460963843895830798/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGgizkLqYX6LGsHECIDnOmjTpL0cTawJCcomdaxosqHBGjAsus=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2025-10-27T07:02:42.389438048Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWT1ptTm9YMkpUTlhKRE9FUkJhWE5hUm1aSVpGRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWT1ptTm9YMkpUTlhKRE9FUkJhWE5hUm1aSVpGRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2a50043a563e5:0xb50959a49d3ce127"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5WOlQwClwoARJ-E8naRZCbU/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25KWWFuRnVjVGRTZG5oUk1IZzVZMGh1VFVOcVMwRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Nothing like a big beautiful warm, sweet butter hug when you walk in the door. It smells amazing and the staff is always friendly. While I have tried their regular croissant, I had not tried the pain au chocolat croissant until today. One crunchy, flaky, delicious, chocolatey mouthful later, I felt a little weak in the knees. Not to mention it's almost the size of your head! Maybe the best chocolate croissant I've ever had. I have also tried their sausage croissant roll & cookies. DELISH ♡♡", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Nothing like a big beautiful warm, sweet butter hug when you walk in the door. It smells amazing and the staff is always friendly. While I have tried their regular croissant, I had not tried the pain au chocolat croissant until today. One crunchy, flaky, delicious, chocolatey mouthful later, I felt a little weak in the knees. Not to mention it's almost the size of your head! Maybe the best chocolate croissant I've ever had. I have also tried their sausage croissant roll & cookies. DELISH ♡♡", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jordan", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110245968161234119424/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIf2EG4HQzwhW5ezXHcchFYU3DHPA8UlBDfpYEBhrOl_tWZ0O3i=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-13T22:55:28.721078235Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25KWWFuRnVjVGRTZG5oUk1IZzVZMGh1VFVOcVMwRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25KWWFuRnVjVGRTZG5oUk1IZzVZMGh1VFVOcVMwRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2a50043a563e5:0xb50959a49d3ce127"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5WOlQwClwoARJ-E8naRZCbU/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSNFowRXlWaTFmYUhCSFNGOVFhVTVwTm5Cc2RWRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Small, cozy, and with some character. It’s an open-kitchen bakery, so you can actually see the team preparing the baked goods, which adds to the cool.\nThe chocolate cookies are a standout and absolutely worth trying. Prices are a little on the higher side, but the quality makes it worth it.\nParking can be hit or miss on the street depending on the time and day, but I usually manage to find a spot in the surrounding neighborhood streets. Otherwise, there’s metered parking available.\nStaff is kind and welcoming. A lovely neighborhood bakery that’s always a pleasure to visit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Small, cozy, and with some character. It’s an open-kitchen bakery, so you can actually see the team preparing the baked goods, which adds to the cool.\nThe chocolate cookies are a standout and absolutely worth trying. Prices are a little on the higher side, but the quality makes it worth it.\nParking can be hit or miss on the street depending on the time and day, but I usually manage to find a spot in the surrounding neighborhood streets. Otherwise, there’s metered parking available.\nStaff is kind and welcoming. A lovely neighborhood bakery that’s always a pleasure to visit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "F T", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112948532467767873572/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWETuQTXaUNzONBBoTy1P5fhR0ucAb5IA75hN6BOKFL36_FMrE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-09T02:45:18.642773100Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSNFowRXlWaTFmYUhCSFNGOVFhVTVwTm5Cc2RWRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSNFowRXlWaTFmYUhCSFNGOVFhVTVwTm5Cc2RWRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2a50043a563e5:0xb50959a49d3ce127"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5WOlQwClwoARJ-E8naRZCbU/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kT2VpMXdXSEZuV21OU1JFVjNjR3d3WlZOaWNrRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "The croissants were so delicious and fresh and crispy! The chocolate chip cookie was soooo good and warm too. The people working were also super friendly and welcoming! There was a little line but it goes super fast!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "The croissants were so delicious and fresh and crispy! The chocolate chip cookie was soooo good and warm too. The people working were also super friendly and welcoming! There was a little line but it goes super fast!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Michelle Khairzad", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106963927486427729008/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKgE_Uiy2iyeJrXixzBRpW5uIaAzZTWa0Et4EJKFedUO_xEwQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-17T17:43:20.403278724Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kT2VpMXdXSEZuV21OU1JFVjNjR3d3WlZOaWNrRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21kT2VpMXdXSEZuV21OU1JFVjNjR3d3WlZOaWNrRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2a50043a563e5:0xb50959a49d3ce127"}, {"name": "places/ChIJ5WOlQwClwoARJ-E8naRZCbU/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21SZlRuY3habkpuVkdaNWRVNVlOVXRUV0hrMFZrRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Are the lines worth the wait? Absolutely. Are they some of the best pastries in LA specifically? Yes, indeed. I think Brent Cox of the Infatuation has the best review of this place, where he describes the croissants as technically perfect, and…”more crackly than flaky, with a delicate honeycomb interior and spirals more beautiful than anything Tom Brady ever threw.”", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Are the lines worth the wait? Absolutely. Are they some of the best pastries in LA specifically? Yes, indeed. I think Brent Cox of the Infatuation has the best review of this place, where he describes the croissants as technically perfect, and…”more crackly than flaky, with a delicate honeycomb interior and spirals more beautiful than anything Tom Brady ever threw.”", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Andrew Keaveney", "uri": "http